oving back to austin it took me a while to find the right barber and luckily the best one in town had just set up shop around the corner from my house the place is immaculate  definitely the style that id want to have in my own house and he always has good music on characterwise im not sure why some people have said hes an ahole is he the most affable person in the world probably not but hes hilarious and you just have to get him started one time he and i rescued some baby birds that were separated from their mother and trying to cross a busy street in front of his shop would an ahole do that ive been going every month for the last two years and i hope that he renews his lease so that i can keep going there for many years to come ive been coming to get my haircut here for a little over a year and todd never fails to make me look my absolute best i receive frequent compliments on my hair from strangers and ive referred several friends here as well todd takes great pride in his work and is very meticulous and consistent i always walk out of here feeling great and knowing i look good the shop is very clean and stylish i love the decor and music it really feels like a more classical barbershop todd keeps a supply of topnotch handpicked products in stock ive switched over to using what he carries and ive never looked back im also thoroughly impressed at todds desire to improve his craft he goes to trade shows all over the world to learn new techniques and sample the latest products it definitely shows in the quality of his haircuts too you will not be disappointed at r todd fisher ive been todds client for seven years hes the kind of man youre jealous of because he makes a living off his talent what he does for a living and what hes really good at are one and the same remarkably gifted is another way to put him ive walked into a bar and had total strangers approach me and ask whered you get your hair done for years ive received compliments from friends old and new because of his work hes not rushed hes precise meticulous the standard haircut service is a  to  minute affair he will go over time if it isnt flawless he will get the fade blend or disconnect perfect the portfolio on his site shows how well he does polished classic and modern styles not only is that true but he can just as easily do more messy and edgy looks which im often after outside of business hours hes continuing to refine his craft by traveling and attending various conferences to consume and learn as much as he can and its paid off clearly he now has his own place he chooses his own product he has his own apprentices you really ought to try him i enjoy my visits to his shop he was clearly taught the art of southern hospitality hell greet you with a hug offer you a drink in the chair hes smart has an attractive sense of humor hes conversational and charming but if all you want is to relax quietly hes just as sensitive to that as well his store is never noisy its never crowded its never rushed todd also stocks quality product including my new favorites imperial and layrite for years ive preferred kevin murphy but ive switched to both of these alternatives at his recommendation and i love them other yelpers have already mentioned the various positives and i agree clean and attractive storefront excellent taste in music selections online scheduling is easy todd will schedule for you at the store if you cant tip bring cash to avoid a small card fee when paying a final reflection on most occasions i try my best to trick todd into giving me a bad haircut its never worked ill arrive with some wild idea about what i want to try next with my hair im also a terrible communicator none of this really hinders todd in the slightest he listens talks me through it makes a couple suggestions of his own and then works his magic all these years ive never sat in the chair feeling nervous only excited and all these years ive never gotten out of the chair feeling upset only happy the two stars is for elegant interior design good music and complimentary drinks im a pretty particular guy im an eye surgeon in training a model and a man with a unique style who knows what he wants i payed up this time  vs  to experience a cut by the owner himself todd i walked in with a minimanbunlength hair and showed him multiple pictures of exactly the look i desired the style sported by christian bale in american psycho and matt bomer in white collar  both pretty consistent elegant and classic relatively longhaired looks allaround shorter than my initial length the cut i received looks like rachel maddows short on the sides  back and longer on the top still significantly shorter than my goal now shes a handsome lady and my cut is not objectively bad its just not the one i ordered imagine going to a restaurant ordering a  steak and receiving a fish filet instead will i survive and do i still look presentable yes it will however take me months to grow my hair out to my desired length the other thing that irked me is the attitude i received how old is that picture dont you want a hairdo in style i replied i have my own style the response then why are you showing me pics of someone elses todd my man a picture is worth a thousand words if i was sporting the cut in the pic i wouldnt be sitting in front of you the styles i showed you are classic and significantly more aesthetic in my eyes than the shortonthesideslongeronthetop look every hipster from here to sf  wburg is sporting the bottom line happiness is the difference between expectations and reality in medicine weve learned we can no longer get away with practicing paternalistically we have to take the patients desires into account and arrive at a shared decision before action is taken barbering is even more aestheticallyoriented just listen to your customers look at their pics and give them what they want unless they give you free rein and they will love you for it it was such a relief to find todd about a year and a half ago he is extremely detailed and consistent with his cuts ive never been disappointed and i always look forward to my appointment i seriously doubt there are many barbers in austin that can match todds expertise his shop is also immaculate and hes fun to talk to ive been getting my hair cut by todd for over five years now across three different locations my cut is fairly simple but has some challenge points that todd is able to navigate with great skill i always come out of his shop looking my best and feeling like ive had a great experience the new storefront on mueller blvd is one of the nicest barber shops ive ever seen great music complimentary drinks and classic styling enhance the overall experience i always look forward to my monthly appointments with todd for a cut and rudy for a shave and beard trim these are my spa days and a great way to step back from lifes daily stresses and just relax for a couple hours easy online scheduling is just an added benefit but be sure to book early as todds schedule fills up quickly especially if youre looking for a weekend appointment reviews here for todd alternate from great barber to total ahole and i wouldnt know about the former but i can attest to the latter the shop on mueller is nice clean and full of vinyl records appointments are relatively hassle free online these would earn stars except when youre refused service they stop mattering i asked for a cut that i could wash and go without product to which he responded then i am not your barber no warning of what might happen without product nor any sales pitch for the value of mens hair products not even a list of cuts that might work without product surely there are some he simply had me leave i took off work planned for weeks walked through the rain theres no parking in front and was rudely refused service of course in the end hes correct hes not my barber so if youre looking for a barber and you want to use buy product i guess you could go here but dont say i didnt warn you todd has been cutting my hair for  years now he is professional skilled and affordable if you are looking to maintain your style or get a new one he has done  for me todd is your guy he has never once been late or canceled on me hes good at what he does and a hoot to chat with beautiful yet manly classy shop my husband loves coming here he is always greeted in a friendly respectful manner and the prices are reasonable when first impressions mattered the most our wedding job interviews etc he trusted the team here at r todd fisher sergio was our go to guy but my husband will continue to come here go see rudy definitely attention to detail top notch place and was so glad i found this place i look forward to going back havent found a good consistent barber in vegas so looks like i will be visiting austin more often make an appointment as they are busy although they did accept me as a walkin todd is hands down the best barber i have ever been too i was in the military for seven years and had to get weekly haircuts  so ive seen my fair share of barbers i love that he takes pride in his work is extremely detail orientated doesnt rush and is great to talk too ive tried other barbers in austin and the quality of service todd provides is second to none even when he has a busy day he doesnt try to get me in and out as quick as he can previous barbers did this several times which led to a horrible cut i dont have to worry about this with todd the compliments i routinely receive from friends and colleagues demonstrate that todd consistently provides a great haircut he knows what looks good trust him and you wont be disappointed let me start by saying this is  the most soul crushing haircut ive ever received im a guy with a unique look sometimes its longer and sometimes its shorter but i have a certain look and feel to my hair  ive had it my whole life its gone now totally devastated i had longer hair going in and i asked for the same shape but within  seconds