citation needed as an adult his technical and creative experience in professional technical and creative experience began in the s fisher is a member of the american society of cinematographerscitation needed in the early s fisher worked with trinity broadcasting network where he wrote produced and directed the comedy television program nightlight starring as satirical television evangelist reverend hype the show was modeled on the nbc program saturday night live and featured actors and comedians such as dan aykroyd jerry houser miguel ferrer rene russo and bernie leadon in  he produced his first feature film twogether starring nick cassavetes and brenda bakkecitation needed architectural design and sound engineeringedit in  fishers mother began curating a large collection of hollywood memorabilia starting with purchasing items from the metrogoldwynmayer auction that same year she spent  which accounted for the purchase of thousands of items serving as the beginning of her ownership of movie memorabilia in  she established the hollywood motion picture museum hmpm as a federally taxexempt corporation the museum has been recognized as the largest individual collection of hollywood memorabilia in the world in  reynolds and her husband richard hamlett bought the paddlewheel hotel  casino at auction for  million the purchase was made in anticipation of spending  million on renovations which included plans for establishing a home for the hollywood motion picture museum the paddlewheel hotel  casino reopened in  renamed the debbie reynolds hotel  casino in  fisher designed the hotel and casinos seat showroom where reynolds performed her nightclub act songs from her career of over  years in the entertainment industry the showroom also serves as a complete television production studio in addition to the showroom fisher also conceived and designed the hollywood motion picture museum when reynolds struggled with the financing to complete the project she decided to take the company public in order to raise funds when the museum celebrated its opening the following year it was one of the first sites in the united states to exhibit highdefinition video projection hotel casino and museum managementedit in march  fisher was appointed the chief financial officer and treasurer of the debbie reynolds hotel  casino joining his mother who served as chairman and secretary with both holding seats on the board of directors when he assumed the role of cfo it became evident that the hotel and casino was losing money each month due to the companys poor capital structure and unsuccessful lease with the casino operator debbie eventually won a  million judgment in court against her former husband richard hamlett in part for spurious financial dealing with the hotel and her personally additional board members of the hollywood museum have included carrie fisher director george lucas shirley maclaine and elizabeth taylor upon assuming the role of ceo fisher began restructuring the company in order to address financial mismanagement diminished employee morale and poor customer service and quality throughout the hotel casino and restaurant prior to march   jackpot enterprises contracted with the company to lease space to operate the casino in the hotel the company gave notice of intent to terminate the lease agreement with jackpot in february  in accordance with the terms owing to monthly loss of revenue on a consistent basis gambling operations discontinued as of march   by december   the company was in default unable to make principal and interest payments on their mortgage payroll taxes of approximately  along with other accounts payable and accrued liabilities of approximately  were also in default in  fisher began pursuing avenues to sell the property to timeshare developer ilx now known as diamond resorts international for  million after the deal fell through debbie reynolds hotel  casino filed chapter  bankruptcy as part of a reorganization plan the company entered into a  million merger agreement with cfi central florida investments also known as westgate resorts which would have saved the hotel and the public company the unsecured creditors rejected the deal and opted to auction the property hoping for a better deal over the objection of management the property was put up for auction the following year with the winning bid at  million going to the world wrestling federation by  reynolds and fisher began preparing to move the hollywood motion picture museum to a new location near the kodak theater in los angeles which was scheduled to open in  when the los angeles museums lender could no longer fund the project the museum was unable to complete construction on the property in turn they could not repay a  million bridge loan which later became the center of a lawsuit filed against the museum by gregory orman while the lawsuit between the museum and orman waged on in the courts the museum signed a deal to anchor the proposed belle island village tourist attraction which was scheduled to debut in fall  in pigeon forge tennessee when the developer of the belle island village resort met with financial struggles of their own the construction lender regions bank foreclosed on the unfinished property in response the museum itself sought chapter  protection in june  the bank initially agreed to sell the resort property to tennessee investment partners which is partially owned by the real estate investment firm of matisse capital the original developer of the proposed belle island village the purchase was scheduled to close by the end of march  with assurances that the buyer intended to reinstate the hollywood motion picture museum as the centerpiece attraction of the new resort the deal additionally called for agreements for the new investor to cover the lawsuit and financial claim made by orman when the sale of the property to tennessee investment partners and subsequent plans to relocate the museum to tennessee fell through reynolds and fisher began making plans to liquidate the memorabilia collection hollywood memorabilia auctionsedit in  reynolds and fisher contracted with profiles in history to begin auctioning the collection of hollywood memorabilia until enough proceeds were generated to pay off their creditors in statements made to the press fisher announced that his mother was heartbroken to have to auction off her collection which was valued at  million in the bankruptcy filing the collection was sold in a series of auctions from june to december  on june   marilyn monroes subway dress whose skirt is raised by the updraft of a passing subway train in the seven year itch sold for  million far in excess of preauction estimates of – million another monroe dress worn in gentlemen prefer blondes fetched  million it had been expected to go for  to  estimated at  to  a blue cotton dress judy garland used in test shots for the wizard of oz went for  in total the auction grossed  million in the second auction held on december   a stillfunctioning panavision psr  mm camera used to film star wars went for  breaking records for star wars memorabilia and vintage cameras filmographyedit acting  a visit with debbie reynolds short – as baby  debbie reynolds and the sound of children tv movie – as cub scout  nightlight tbn series – as reverend hype  these old broads tv movie – as timothy as himself  hollywood without makeup documentary  hollywood treasure cinematography  find your way back a salute to the space shuttle video documentary  blue angels a backstage pass video documentary  cinerama adventure documentary  south dakota directing  movie memories with debbie reynolds tv series –  episodes editing  twogether producing  twogether  bright lights starring carrie fisher and debbie reynolds hbo documentary referencesedit  a b debbie reynolds has son the new york times february   p  retrieved december   miss reynolds gave birth to the child at st josephs hospital in burbank  abstract full 